President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday urged migrants to within six months submit themselves for e-registration at the Nigeria Immigration Service Headquarters, Abuja. Buhari said government has the right to know each migrant adding that the registrations process will further enhance the internal security of the country. The President, who was represented at the official commissioning of the Migrant e-registration Center and passport data processing center by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Boss Mustapha, said government is serious over the development. He advised migrants to take advantage of the six months amnesty period to avoid penalty. Details shortly…….